Package: xtop
Version: 0.40.0-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: journalctl, docker-compose, postgresql-client
Installed-Size: 23300
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 xtop is a terminal-based system monitor with ranked root-cause hypotheses,
 evidence scoring, and eBPF deep diagnostics. v0.40.0 adds a full-filesystem
 polite big-file scanner (ionice IDLE class + adaptive IO pacing, opt-in via
 XTOP_DEEP_SCAN=1) plus elevated inode-usage visibility across the disk
 section. Includes everything from 0.39.x: SRE Resource Share panel on Apps
 page, multi-host fleet hub with web dashboard, incident diff, config drift,
 app-log + OTel correlation, runbook library, postmortem tooling, VM cost
 right-sizing, named baselines, Kubernetes pod-aware view, confidence
 calibration, skew-aware CUSUM change-point detection.
